        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 2:18PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Bellevue, or 11 miles east of Henrietta, moving east
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Montague County, including the following locations... Belcherville
and Ringgold.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
